data.name: Space Elevator Lab
data.description: PLUTO-CHARON ELEVATOR - Pluto and its moon Charon are tidally locked. A tether between the two stretches 17,800 km.
data.rawText: Your factory-assisted landings/liftoffs anywhere treat lander burns as normal Burn Spaces.

data.name: GEO Elevator Bernal
data.description: SPACE ELEVATOR - Centripedal force holds the elevator cable vertical over its anchorage.
data.rawText: Bernal SPACE ELEVATOR 10 MASS 6 Rad-Hard HOME: Boost direct to Home Bernal in GEO without doubling boost costs. Time to GEO: 7.5 days Power: 4 MW (beamed) Climber Mass: 20 Mtonne

data.name: Climate Control Lab
data.description: L1 MOIRE LENS SUNSHADE - A concave rotating Fresnel lens diverts sunlight to or from a planet for climate engineering.
data.rawText: +2 VP per Dirtside for this Bernal.

data.name: L1 Climate Control Bernal
data.description: L1 SPACE MIRROR SWARM - A swarm of sail-mirrors in the Sol-Earth L1 Lagrange to divert sunlight for climate engineering.
data.rawText: HOME: You are always the 1st player, superseding all other claimants.

data.name: Collimator Lab
data.description: DYSON SWARM POWERSATS - A power-beaming swarm of thousands of sun-fired lasers in inclined orbits.
data.rawText: Gain the Powersat faction privilege. Powersat push includes a Bonus Pivot.

data.name: L2 Collimator Bernal
data.description: OPTICAL TELESCOPE - Shown is one of many in a precision formation located in the Earth-Luna L2 point.
data.rawText: HOME: Gain the Powersat faction privilege.

data.name: Lofstrom Loop Microgravity Lab
data.description: MASS DRIVER PROPULSION - Equipped with an electromagnetic railgun, a Bernal sacrifices its own dirt shielding for thrust.
data.rawText: Your factory-assisted landings/liftoffs anywhere treat lander burns as normal Burn Spaces.

data.name: L3 Lofstrom Loop Microgravity
data.description: LAUNCH LOOP - Accelerates humans & cargos to escape velocity.
data.rawText: HOME: Boost direct to Home Bernal without doubling boost costs.

data.name: Antimatter Lab
data.description: BERNAL SPHERE - A sphere is optimal for air pressure maintenance and minimal radiation shielding.
data.rawText: Your Crew has an On-Board Nuclear Any reactor.

data.name: L4 Antimatter Factory
data.description: LINAC Amat Factory - Cascading debris from a proton beam target are sorted to extract isotope fuels, then positrons and antiprotons.
data.rawText: HOME: Your Crew has an On-Board Nuclear Any reactor.

data.name: Pharmaceutics Lab
data.description: PHARMING BEADED TORUS - Breeds neogenic organelles that function to reverse human disorders arising from radiation and weightlessness. Pharm Module Diameter: 100m, Inhabitants: 48
data.rawText: Gain the Skunkworks faction privilege & impose academia hand limit on all opponents.

data.name: L4s Pharmaceutics Bernal
data.description: BOLO HABITAT - A dumbell geometry minimizes hull mass, although more shielding mass is needed. Mass: 17t (hull), 7t (air), Rotation: 3 rpm, Inhabitants: 15
data.rawText: HOME: Gain the Skunkworks faction privilege.

data.name: Solar Cell Lab
data.description: SUN-FIRED WPT POWER BEAM - A bio-mimetic array of solar concentrators generating microwave power. WPT Frequency: 2.45 GHz, Power: 500 MWbeam, Efficiency: 34%, Mass: 12 ktonnes
data.rawText: +2 to the Net Thrust of your Spacecraft that use Solar-Power.

data.name: L5 Solar Cell Factory
data.description: SOLAR CELL FACTORY - Photovoltaic cells are conveyed through vapor deposition sections, then cut and integrated into panels and arrays. Length: 400m, Power: 240 MWe, Throughput: 14 ktons/yr, Inhabitants: 110
data.rawText: HOME: +1 to the Net Thrust of your Spacecraft that use Solar-Power.

data.name: Cancer Lab
data.description: STANFORD TORUS - Primary and secondary mirrors direct sunlight into the interior. Radius: 56m (major), 7m (minor), Mass: 80t (hull), 60t (air), Rotation: 4 rpm, Inhabitants: 123
data.rawText: Gain +1 Token VP for each Colony Dome. Your Crew and Human Colonists have a rad-hard of at least 7.

data.name: L5s Cancer Hospital
data.description: NAUTILUS-X - Parked in a Lagrange point for long duration missions. Uses a centrifuge for the investigation of microgravity on human health. Crew: 6
data.rawText: HOME: You are immune to budget cuts.

data.name: Diplomatic Lab
data.description: O'NEIL SUNFLOWER - Twin cylinders rotate about their center of gravity. The mirrors admit sunlight without allowing cosmic rays to bypass the shielded area. Rotation: 2 rpm, Cylinder Diameter: 1 km
data.rawText: (Module 0) Your delegates in the assembly are +1 VP each.

data.name: SSO Diplomatic
data.description: INTERNATIONAL SPACE STATION - A habitat in LEO, launched 1998. Mass: 420 tonnes (Mass 10), Length: 51m, Inhabitants: 6
data.rawText: HOME: (Module 0) Your delegates in the Ideology of your Faction color are +1 VP each.

data.name: Tourism Hotel
data.description: MCKENDREE CYLINDER - Similar to an O'Neill Cylinder, but using carbon nanotube construction instead of steel. Cylinder: 70m long, 70m dia, Inhabitants: 700
data.rawText: +2 VP per Dirtside for this Bernal.

data.name: Tourism Cycler
data.description: 2:1 RESONANCE CYCLER - Kalpana cylinder passes monthly through the VAB as it cycles between Earth and Luna. Cylinder: 56m long, 56m dia, Unshielded Mass: 8.5 ktonnes, Hull Mass: 500 tonnes, Rotation: 4 rpm, Inhabitants: 490
data.rawText: HOME: Can designate any Spacecraft to forgo Belt Rolls in the Radiation Belts near Earth.

data.name: Force Field Lab
data.description: Military grade active shielding to protect ionized particles from solar wind using superconducting magnets forming a Langevin field.
data.rawText: Bernal 10 MASS 10 Rad-Hard S HOME: Gain the Powersat refuel priv. Military grade active shielding Force Field Lab

data.name: L2 Force Field Bernal
data.description: Intended for protection against low-energy ions on either side of the solar wind behind charged plasma windows.
data.rawText: Bernal 10 MASS 10 Rad-Hard S HOME: Gain the Powersat refuel priv. L2 Force Field Bernal

data.name: Catcher's Mitt Lab
data.description: CATCHER'S MITT - High per-word cost to repurpose orbital node for chemical or rail launch from LEO to cislunar sites.
data.rawText: Bernal 10 MASS 6 Rad-Hard E HOME: Gain the Powersat refuel priv. Catcher's Mitt Lab

data.name: Catcher's Mitt Bernal
data.description: CATCHER'S MITT - Clean Space One concept for orbital debris removal and recycling. Mass: 420 tonnes, Length: 40m, Inhabitants: 4
data.rawText: Bernal 10 MASS 6 Rad-Hard E HOME: Gain the Powersat refuel priv. Catcher's Mitt Bernal

data.name: Babbage Halbonauts
data.description: A Halbonaut is guided by a HAL Turing or other central controller. Its Babbage circuitry, (mechanical analogs of electronic transistors) withstands high radiation and temperature.

data.name: Utility Fog Halbonaut
data.description: A shape-shifting flux-pinned network of nanobots under the control of a Turing CPU.

data.name: Group Mind Immortalists
data.description: When the Global Brain leads to universal intelligence, reduced aging, and an immortal techno-society as neurons of a benign death.

data.name: Biomechs
data.description: Biomechatronics integrates biology, mechanics, and electronics for improved respiration, vision, metabolism, and artificial limbs.

data.name: Soldier Caste
data.description: The military arm of the current polity.

data.name: Botany Bay Convicts
data.description: The New Botany Bay Penal Colony is the answer to severe labor shortages in space.

data.name: Martian Assembly
data.description: Government based on Mars which builds space elevators.

data.name: Boyle Engineering Collective
data.description: Mars Nativism protects the rights of the First Hundred and native-born against those born on Earth.

data.name: Wet-Nano Seed Sail
data.description: Precision biomimetic nano-technology (wet nano) builds any artifacts materials along with complex carbohydrates.

data.name: Calypso 2 Seed Sail
data.description: Named after the legendary oceanographic research vessel used by Jacques-Ives Cousteau. A closed eco-system allows low mass. Its mission is to spread life to other worlds.

data.name: New Attica Secessionists
data.description: Demanding Earth isn't rule it dynamically, the secessionists threaten space-based reprisals to gain independence.

data.name: Heavy Water Survivalists
data.description: Libertarians, survivalists, and doomsayers convinced that the Earth is kaput. They drink heavy water (D2O) to improve radiation resistance.

data.name: Iceworms
data.description: Iceworms are skilled at tunneling through ice, and live in submarine colonies in Outer Solar.

data.name: House of Saud
data.description: The ruling royal family of Saudi Arabia is the richest dynasty in history.

data.name: Rental Body Guild
data.description: Guild members teleuperate rented bodies while their actual bodies are in quiescent nearby.

data.name: Juiced Cosmonauts
data.description: Drugs hold against the harsh conditions.

data.name: Svalbard Caretakers
data.description: Taking the long road to the future, only tech caretakers will industrialized by any player.

data.name: Lloyd's Salvage Co.
data.description: Policy of replacing corporate transactions with individual ones, enabled by reputation tracking and easily-created microsatellite infrastructure.

data.name: Renaissance Man
data.description: A renaissance man is a wearer of varied talents and learning.

data.name: Malcolm
data.description: An eccentric tycoon determined to make his mark in the High Frontier.

data.name: Blue Goo Sybonts
data.description: A hybrid body is enriched with organisms, synthetic plasma, bacteria, and a bio-based system called blue goo.

data.name: Microgravity Pantrophists
data.description: Pantropy is the practice of adapting to an environment rather than altering it, by use of gene-spliced biological symbionts.

data.name: Programmable Matter
data.description: Changes its physical properties (shape, density, moduli, conductivity, or optical properties) in accordance with autonomous programming.

data.name: Neumann Matter
data.description: Neumanns are reprogrammable programmable matter. Each manipulator arm launches of microscopic Van Neumann free.

data.name: Alchemist Aviatrices
data.description: Carrier skycyclists use electromagnets to purify the reagents & isotopes required for rockets.

data.name: Rock Rats Miners' Union
data.description: Human-cobot teams optimize productivity in extreme conditions, including weightlessness and low gravity.

data.name: Security System
data.description: Provides collision protection using radar-guided lasers that nudge incoming debris off course.

data.name: Frankenstein Navigator
data.description: A digital navigator combines the advantages of a digital mind with the self-repair and reproductive-reality of a humanoid.

data.name: Josephson Implants
data.description: Hackers implanted with flux quantum superconducting quantum computers are the result of a secret KSS project.

data.name: Siren Cybernautics Inc.
data.description: Space-hardened radiation and bone atrophy, the space employees of Siren Cybernautics live in the Trojans using high-oxygen PFCs, breathing with liquid-filled lungs.

data.name: Smart Pets
data.description: Lab animals enhanced with brain-computer interface technology. This device can be 3D-printed & applied to any lab rat to make it into a work animal.

data.name: Creeper Neogen
data.description: Crawling creeper genes form a chimera of invertebrate DNA. Fully biological, organs and able to reproduce like any other organism.

data.name: Kaluga Naniteers
data.description: An engineering discipline skilled in nanobots and nanocables composed of graphenecarbon Tsiolkovsky's hermitage.

data.name: Transorbital Railworkers
data.description: Started from a small federally-subsidized launching operation, which boasts years in LEO and has become payload space between cislunar space.

data.name: Eugenic Pilgrims
data.description: We regard tinkering with the God-given genome as singerant a corruption. We offer ourselves the old-fashioned way, by controlled breeding.

data.name: Vatican Observers
data.description: In the tradition of the Forbidden Observatory, it is the Vatican's attempt to oversee the direction of technology and science.

data.name: Beowulf Internet
data.description: The woodcarved network of mass-produced networked computer nodes, each one dumber than a smartphone, but in vast communication delays hindered by interplanetary comm.

data.name: Grendel
data.description: In Beowulf legend, Grendel is a monstrous shadow-walker who menaces those who travel between Heorots.

data.name: Combat Quadrupeds
data.description: Weaponized patrol the perimeters of human settlements, our bots have highly agile and specialized terrain.

data.name: Lernaean Warbots
data.description: Biomechanically weaponized robots, bio-hardened being fight with no vital spots.

data.name: Nano-3D Printers
data.description: With a sufficiently microscopic precision, 3D-printers assemble complex or exotic structures at a nanoscale level of detail.

data.name: Offworld Replicators
data.description: Can reproduce autonomously by extracting & manipulating the plastics and assemblies necessary to duplicate itself.

data.name: Apex Algorithms
data.description: With artificial singularity attained the technology, growth of exponential power begins to grow.

data.name: Self-designing Heuristics
data.description: With the help of heuristics or rules of thumb & genetic algorithms and real-time inference, it is possible to imbue machinery with a source code able to adapt to uncodified designs.

data.name: Cobots
data.description: Intelligent humaniform robots optimized to collaborate with humans. Includes a level of collective mind underpinned by IoT.

data.name: Singularity
data.description: With significantly, more powerful than human language, could an algorithm capable of self-deep learning lead to an intelligence that can evolve self-interests?

data.name: Sensor Web Sail
data.description: A mesh of flex-wires with sensors and power cells to the mesh spacing.

data.name: Wisp
data.description: With a sufficiently microscopic precision, space solar array can be printed with nano-layers.

data.name: Inner Tour
data.destination: Enter 4 different flyby Spaces in the same Turn.
data.fulfilledAbility: when entering Aerobrake Hazards leading to LEO.
data.flavorText: Using flybys, it is possible to see a great deal of the inner system in a short period of time.

data.name: Grand Tour
data.destination: Enter 2 flyby Spaces beyond Ceres zone in the same Turn.
data.flavorText: The Grand Tour was the mission of Voyager 2 visiting the giant planets using slingshots.

data.name: Vanity Project
data.destination: Enter any Inner Moon or Helion Return (7G/0G).
data.flavorText: The very silly, especially a very rich silly, like to fly in the face of danger.

data.name: Extreme Sports
data.destination: Enter any Moon in a hazard zone with a Torch Engine and 3 G-hours of burns in the same Turn.
data.flavorText: The very geeky and very rich are willing to pay big bucks for playing ships on dangerous fly-bys.

data.name: Fugitive
data.destination: Enter any ET Colony when your Faction suffers Anarchy.
data.flavorText: Independent digital colonies allow a person's consciousness to exist and be propagated despite poor local governance.

data.name: Refugees
data.flavorText: Humanitarian groups are willing to pay top dollar to save people not served by the current governance system.

data.name: Chiron Quest
data.flavorText: Named after a gentle centaur in Greek mythology, Chiron circles between Saturn and Uranus and is potentially covered with tarry hydrocarbons.

data.name: Cen Tour
data.flavorText: Chiron is a comet also classified as a Centaur, for its halfway distance between Jupiter and Neptune.

data.name: Hubris
data.flavorText: Although humans have successfully manufactured an environment where one can live in space, arrogance and overconfidence could result in catastrophic system failure.

data.name: Fulgurite Hunt
data.destination: Enter any Site, Prospect or Factory (>=50 mbar).
data.flavorText: Obsessed traveler is willing to pay top dollar to acquire pieces of glass forged by lightning strikes.

data.name: Comet Adventure
data.flavorText: The highly textured world, looking more like a loose collection of rocks than a single coherent rock, has much popular to the fringe communities.

data.name: Pleasure Garden
data.destination: Enter any Site beyond Ceres zone.
data.flavorText: Pornography exists, but mostly in virtual space and is big business. Outer sites that create real porn can make good revenue at the right buyers.

data.name: Robotic Facility
data.flavorText: The space environment is ideal for complex robots. Vacuum keeps them clean and slow spin keeps the facility organized.

data.name: Goo Spores
data.destination: When Fulfilling, must dismantle a bug.
data.flavorText: A gray-goo catastrophe just occurred, and gray-goo spores were ejected beyond the solar system, leaving more spores for research.

data.name: Artemis
data.fulfilledAbility: You may prospect Luna without performing a boost for 1st player.
data.flavorText: Artemis was the goddess of wild animals and hunt and was often identified with the moon. Her legacy continues in modern times through NASA's project.

data.name: HAVOC
data.destination: Enter any Ice or Water Moon (7.00-9.99).
data.flavorText: HAVOC was designed by NASA's Langley Research Center, using dirigibles in Venus's atmosphere where pressure and temperature are more Earth-like.

data.name: New Horizons
data.flavorText: The famous New Horizons probe traveled 9 years without stopping. This mission goes to Kuiper Belt at a leisure pace and pays for those that visit.

data.name: Home on Lagrange
data.destination: Your Anchored Bernal not in Venus/Earth/Mars zones.
data.flavorText: The artificial gravity and cave-like surface of a rotating space station are the best conditions of a safe area to live in space and give birth to children.

data.name: Mars Polar Walk
data.destination: Enter North or South Axial Return (7.5-8.0).
data.flavorText: The North polar ice of Mars extends down to about 45 degrees and is about 2 km. Axial Returns can reach for either pole.

data.name: ET Holy Grail
data.flavorText: Be the first agent to go where no one has explored before.

data.name: Closest Planet
data.flavorText: Settled in the closest planet from the Sun, Mercury is slightly larger than our Moon. It has both the densest and hottest rocks in the Solar System.

data.name: Highest Cliff
data.flavorText: The Verona Rupes on Miranda in the Uranus system is the tallest cliff in the solar system. The 20 km cliff offers one of the best bungee jumping and climbing opportunities.

data.name: Fool's Gold
data.flavorText: A failure in communications makes a trillionaire believe there is a secret motherlode at a comet rendezvous.

data.name: Rivalry
data.destination: Highest Glory chits in hand (of any player).
data.fulfilledAbility: Gain 1 additional Aqua when fulfilling Contracts.
data.flavorText: The celebrity factor of glory chits is enough to satiate this trillionaire with no shortage of money.

data.name: Mercury Forge
data.flavorText: A network of manufacturing plants powered by ISRU-extracted Thorium, provides necessary infrastructure for deep space craft assembly and equipment manufacture.

data.name: Topographic Ocean
data.fulfilledAbility: Gain 4 Aquas when any Colony & Refinery there are built.
data.flavorText: Sublimated vapors burst through recently sealed crevasses in an expanse not only of mountains and valleys but towers and terraces reaching high into the tenuous atmosphere.

data.name: Plasma Intrusion Laboratory
data.fulfilledAbility: +1 flyby bonus from Radiation Ray Gun once/Turn (total +3).
data.flavorText: The Io Torus, or the Io Plasma Torus, is a large torus plasma ring near Jupiter's equator associated with volcanic emissions from the moon Io.

data.name: Triggered Decay Positrons
data.fulfilledAbility: +1 flyby bonus from Radiation Ray Gun once/Turn.
data.flavorText: The triggered release of ions, protons, electrons or positrons (anti-electrons) is a catalytic nuclear reaction.

data.name: Hexapod Explorer
data.flavorText: A rover with a hexapod multi-legged frame, enables the negotiation of boulders and ridges more efficiently than wheels and provides greater overall stability.

data.name: Amalthea Halbonaut
data.flavorText: Amalthea is the most radiation intense body in the solar system. Heavy ion flux, but also includes low energy electrons and positrons.

data.name: Equatorial Launch Railway
data.fulfilledAbility: Acetylene reprocessing lifts all ET Tokens to your Factories.
data.flavorText: A rail track parallel to the celestial equator. Vehicles on the track, may become orbital velocity to the atmosphere and beyond.

data.name: Fullerene Cable Spinner
data.flavorText: Manufacturing facility to produce cables composed of buckminster fullerene (buckyballs) and carbon nanotubes that make incredibly strong cables.

data.name: Solar Observatory
data.flavorText: Sun-diver and circumsolar study. Helioseismology & photosphere evolution and coronal heating.

data.name: Golden Apples of the Sun
data.flavorText: The outermost sublayer of field-shift and is uniform with Earth's, and lies deep in the photosphere.

data.name: Largest Object
data.flavorText: After an unexpected mega outburst of vapor, the Dawn orbiter's camera system observed bright spots on the surface. Ceres is the largest object in the Asteroid Belt.

data.name: Cyborg Transhumans
data.flavorText: Mind to cybernetic unified systems. Human + machine intelligence. Cybernetic organisms are sentient without the limitations of a traditional human form.

data.name: Submersible Prospector
data.flavorText: Explore the depth and likely tidal-powered hydrothermal vents. High degree of automation, precision sensors, mapping technology.

data.name: Goldilocks Luna Terraform
data.fulfilledAbility: You do not need to promote to build Colonies & Factories on Luna.
data.flavorText: Ultra-thin aluminized Mylar/Kapton floated between Luna-Sol to provide shielding.

data.name: Beehive
data.destination: Aldrin Cycler via Buzz of Humankind
data.flavorText: After production of this project deliver the disk projects Swarmfaring, Photon Recycler or Solar Moth.

data.name: Ring Industrialization
data.destination: Saturn (RAD S Site on any Sat. Turn)
data.fulfilledAbility: ring - your Mobile Factories on each WT count as Factories.
data.flavorText: Manufacturing in micro/zero-G on Saturn's Rings is not on solid ground but on floating particle rafts.

data.name: Sun-fired Laser
data.flavorText: A multi-thermal-terawatt laser-relay capable of propelling solar sail vehicles.

data.name: Daedalus Starship Research
data.flavorText: Even proper advanced designs are thousands of times more massive than current technology, rely on unproven physics.

data.name: Green Magnetosphere
data.flavorText: A Green power station utilizing the planet's natural magnetic field. A current flows through the electrical infrastructure.

data.name: Ice Phase Research
data.flavorText: The Quaoar/Weywot system has crystalline ice in contrast to most KBO have amorphous ice.

data.name: Aerover Blimp Explorer
data.flavorText: Reconnaissance blimp can negotiate/maneuver atmospheric conditions better than free-flying buoyant balloons.

data.name: Nuclear Electric Airship
data.flavorText: This reconnaissance airship may remain aloft for weeks or months at a time, has high maneuverability.

data.name: Mosquito
data.flavorText: Low-cost, lightweight, minimalist Martian explorer designed to venture into hard-to-access terrain.

data.name: Solar Nebula Mafics
data.flavorText: Phoebe, likely a TNO interloper, is second only to Earth in compositional diversity.

data.name: Planetary Protection
data.requirements: When Fulfilling: Discard a space up to 3 steps away.
data.flavorText: Careful flag contaminated ISRU technology and site a Robonaut there to bring it up to code.

data.name: Planetary Rail Network
data.destination: Colonized Buoyant (M, N or V) colony (no Io)
data.flavorText: Rails can be established and maintained more easily on planets with no atmosphere to corrode them and low gravity.

data.name: Bio-Inspired Rover
data.flavorText: A bio-inspired rover must explore a world of interest to explore life origins instead of explore for minerals.

data.name: Subnubilar Zeppelin
data.flavorText: Arccloud expansions under the Venus or Neptune clouds create an environment for long-term missions.

data.name: Junket
data.flavorText: A publicity only political or promotional site to bring the public or media up to the colony.

data.name: Spaceborn Political Rally
data.requirements: When Fulfilling: Discard a Political card.
data.flavorText: A political rally organized from Earth to free space with tunnel pads and burrows.

data.name: Drug Smuggling
data.requirements: When Fulfilling: Discard any 3 cards from hand.
data.flavorText: Illegal drugs, vaccine and life-extension therapies are produced at bioengineering colonies through the use of unique microgravity or exotic environments.

data.name: Chipjack
data.destination: Colonized with a 'Bernal' anywhere and beyond Ceres
data.fulfilledAbility: You may perform instant Operations on a Bernal even if occupied by others.
data.flavorText: Infiltrate and steal secret or proprietary documents and technology files.

data.name: Cancer Research Mission
data.flavorText: Allow humans harvesting an unshielded cycler station or interlude with no other life within a few years and return with samples.

data.name: Trojan Listening Posts
data.flavorText: An observatory placed in orbit around or near a Trojan asteroid could provide years of careful scrutiny of deep space operations while hiding in a swarm.

data.name: Rescue Team
data.flavorText: Investigate loss of life at a now-derelict spacecraft or colony. Discover signs of rebellion.

data.name: Mercury Sunset Convoy
data.destination: Colonized M Colony with Mobility (Operational or Outpost)
data.flavorText: Given Mercury's slow orbit this means a very long journey, one that few others can do.

data.name: SWIV Miner
data.flavorText: Prevent ongoing asteroid or comet mining by claiming their next likely collected and mined target.

data.name: Refueling Trawler
data.flavorText: Provide loiter positions for craft refueling or maintenance to provide deep space presence.

data.name: Tsiolkovsky Elevator Lab
data.fulfilledAbility: Your factory-assist Encrustation cannot be Encrusted at other Elevator as normal burn spaces at Earth Spaces.
data.flavorText: Building a working space elevator would be enormously expensive and this research could lead the way.

data.name: Skyhook
data.destination: Your Factory Site at one end of a Space Elevator icon.
data.requirements: When Fulfilling: Build a Space Elevator at this Site (no Hazard Roll).
data.flavorText: A rotating tether in low orbit can boost payloads via momentum transfer.

data.name: Spin Control
data.flavorText: Working out issues on these contact binary anomalies is excellent research for future asteroid deflections.

data.name: Ring Rain
data.flavorText: The ring of giant planets are resupplied by constant impacts on small shepherd moons and meteoroid bombardment.

data.name: Search for Life Center
data.flavorText: Classify the origin of synthesized life to use, an attempt to achieve, and perhaps replicate abiogenesis.

data.name: Sunrise Project
data.flavorText: The industrial revolution happened alongside fossil fuel revolution. Why can we not similarly do the same with solar magnetic power?

data.name: Yarkovsky Research
data.flavorText: The Yarkovsky effect sets small asteroids spiraling inward or outward, changing projected impact targets by centuries.

data.name: Deep Space One
data.flavorText: Uranus is the easiest source for bulk quantities of He-3, nitrogen, and carbon - all in high demand on Earth.

data.name: Hardened Base
data.flavorText: A heavily-shielded, armor-hardened base typically designed for extended operations in hostile environments.

data.name: Classified Security Payload
data.flavorText: [REDACTED]

data.name: United Nations Cosmonauts
data.description: SECRETARY GENERAL: Start the game with +2 Aqua.
data.rawText: Crew A 1 MASS 4 Rad-Hard SECRETARY GENERAL Start the game with +2 Aqua United Nations Cosmonauts

data.name: ROSCOSMOS
data.description: TAXES: +1 Aqua after any player places a Claim or industrializes.
data.rawText: Crew B 1 MASS 5 Rad-Hard TAXES ROSCOSMOS

data.name: Taikonauts
data.description: FELONIOUS: May perform Felonious actions.
data.rawText: Crew C 1 MASS 4 Rad-Hard FELONIOUS Taikonauts

data.name: NASA Astronauts
data.description: LAUNCH FEES: +1 Aqua from the Pool after any player performs a boost operation.
data.rawText: Crew D 1 MASS 4 Rad-Hard LAUNCH FEES NASA Astronauts

data.name: Anonymous P2P
data.description: OPEN SOURCE FINAO: Costs of FINAO is 3 Aqua.
data.rawText: Crew E 1 MASS 4 Rad-Hard OPEN SOURCE FINAO Anonymous P2P

data.name: ESA Space Unionists
data.description: POWERSAT: During any player's turn: May give +1 thrust to any spacecraft that in their thruster triangle has solar.
data.rawText: Crew F 1 MASS 4 Rad-Hard POWERSAT ESA Space Unionists

data.name: ISRO Glavcosmonauts
data.description: DHARMA REFUEL: Double yield from site refuel when carrying a glory chit.
data.rawText: Crew G 1 MASS 4 Rad-Hard DHARMA REFUEL ISRO Glavcosmonauts

data.name: B612 Foundation
data.description: BLINK TELESCOPE: 1 re-roll per prospecting operation when using a Raygun.
data.rawText: Crew H 1 MASS 3 Rad-Hard BLINK TELESCOPE B612 Foundation

data.name: SpaceX
data.description: MARKETEER: Always win Auction ties.
data.rawText: Crew J 1 MASS 4 Rad-Hard MARKETEER SpaceX

data.name: Norse Astronauts
data.description: SCRUM TROUBLESHOOTERS: Repair any Glitch anywhere.
